######## Instructions about the Instalation of Ember Framework


##### Nodejs ---Version v5.7.0
** Command 
curl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_5.x | sudo -E bash -

###### npm ---Version 3.7.5

###### ember ---Version 2.4.1
** Command 
npm install -g ember-cli
 
###### Watchman ---Version 4.5.0
git clone https://github.com/facebook/watchman.git
cd watchman
git checkout v4.5.0
./autogen.sh
./configure    
make   
sudo make install

#### Prerequisites for Watchman
sudo apt-get install automake
sudo apt-get install python-dev

#### Special Configuration for Watchman
cat /proc/sys/fs/inotify/max_user_watches
echo 524288 | sudo tee -a /proc/sys/fs/inotify/max_user_watches


####Add Bootstrap and Sass to Travel Expenses App
* Run the following two commands:
ember install ember-cli-sass
ember install ember-cli-bootstrap-sassy

* Rename the app.css to app.scss:
mv app/styles/app.css app/styles/app.scss

* Open ./app/styles/app.scss and add the following line:
@import "bootstrap";

* Relaunch the app with ember server

####Add Simple Auth Library & Simple Auth Token Plugin
* ember install ember-simple-auth
* ember-simple-auth-token

####Add Truth Helpers library
* npm install ember-truth-helpers --save

####Add ember-text-limit adon
*  ember install ember-text-limit


#### Run the app 
cd /appDirectory

** Command 
* ember serve
* Ctrl+C: stops the ember server




